          <div class="review-title">David Seaman · 5.0 out of 5 stars · It works</div>
          <div class="review-meta">Reviewed in the United States on November 27, 2022 · Format: Paperback · Verified Purchase</div>
          <div class="review-body">
            <p>Not only have I found this program to be salvation, I participated in the study with Dr. Lisa Najavits at Harvard/McLean.</p>
            <p>The program works but it requires a commitment from the patient. Each visit requires an outside commitment which the patient chooses. It can be speaking to a conflicted family member, applying for a job, reading pertinent documents, really anything that will keep you moving forward. I chose to write, focusing on how my life was formed by trauma and the uselessness of self medication.</p>
            <p>The premise is to be made to feel safe during sessions and the well trained therapist with whom I met three times a week was good at this. In order to re-visit past trauma, a necessity in healing, you must feel safe.</p>
            <p>This manual is a breakthrough for treatment.</p>
