        <article class="review-card">
          <div class="review-title">Elizabeth · 5.0 out of 5 stars · Oops for clinicians</div>
          <div class="review-meta">Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2020 · Format: Paperback · Verified Purchase</div>
          <div class="review-body">
            <p>I purchased this as a patient but I think it will be okay. No jargon so far and really helpful worksheets. If you feel lost by the distance between these two diagnoses this book will really help. It is the basis for support groups and excerpts used in my IOP, so considered top rate by professionals. A very compassionate work.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="review-helpful">5 people found this helpful</div>
